<task id="020" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P1.D1 — Flip enforce_admins:true on master branch protection (FR-09)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completed-date>2026-05-31</completed-date>
    <completion-summary>FR-09 satisfied. `gh api -X POST repos/spaarke-dev/spaarke/branches/master/protection/enforce_admins` returned `{"enabled":true}`. Pre-flip state captured to `baseline/branch-protection-pre-FR09-2026-05-31.json` + `baseline/ci-gate-pre-flip-2026-05-31.json`; post-flip state captured to `baseline/ci-gate-post-flip-2026-05-31.json`. All 3 required status contexts (`Build &amp; Test (Debug)`, `Build &amp; Test (Release)`, `Code Quality`) verified intact. NFR-01 satisfied (only `baseline/` writes). Rollback command for posterity: `gh api -X DELETE repos/spaarke-dev/spaarke/branches/master/protection/enforce_admins` (per D-02 reassessment trigger — NOT a casual operation). See `current-task.md` Task 020 Execution Log for full diff + binding-constraint compliance matrix.</completion-summary>
    <estimated-effort>15-30 minutes</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent (with operator admin token)</assigned>
    <tags>phase-1, ci-gate, governance, p1-d</tags>
    <parallel-group>1-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>GitHub API only; no file system writes; disjoint from all sibling Wave 1-A tasks (010, 011, 012, 013, 015, 017, 021, 022, 024)</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Flip `enforce_admins: true` on the `master` branch protection for the required status checks:
    `Build & Test (Debug)`, `Build & Test (Release)`, `Code Quality`. This is the load-bearing
    change that converts the BFF CI gate from "fictional" (10/10 recent runs failed, code shipped
    anyway) to "operational."

    REQUIRES admin token (operator's GH PAT or `gh auth status` showing admin scope). If the AI
    agent's environment does NOT have admin scope, HALT and request operator to execute the
    `gh api` PUT call.

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-01: no code changes (this is GitHub API config, not file edits).
    Per design.md §5.2: full enforce_admins is the only robust option; anything less recreates
    the rot mechanism.
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent (or operator-assisted agent) applying GitHub branch protection via gh CLI.</role>

  <goal>
    `gh api repos/spaarke-dev/spaarke/branches/master/protection` returns JSON with
    `enforce_admins.enabled: true`. Required status checks include all three:
    `Build & Test (Debug)`, `Build & Test (Release)`, `Code Quality`.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="baseline-ci">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/ci-gate-snapshot-2026-MM-DD.json</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">No source/production code modifications</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-09">enforce_admins must be true for all 3 named status checks</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md §5.2">No partial enforcement; full enforce_admins is the binding decision</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §3.5 the current branch protection on master shows `enforce_admins: false`.
      This is the bypass mechanism that enabled "10 of 10 most recent CI runs failed but code
      merged and shipped anyway." Restoring the CI gate WITHOUT closing this bypass is theater.
      Per design.md §5.2, the only robust option is full enforce_admins; partial enforcement
      (e.g., "enforce only on Code Quality but not on Build & Test") would let the same rot
      recur on different checks.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="001" status="not-started">Baseline CI gate snapshot exists (shows current enforce_admins: false)</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>(none — GitHub API call only; no file system writes other than verification artifact)</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Verify admin scope: run `gh auth status`. If output does NOT show admin scope (or token belongs to non-admin user), HALT and request operator to run the call.</step>
    <step order="2">Capture pre-change snapshot: `gh api repos/spaarke-dev/spaarke/branches/master/protection > projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/ci-gate-pre-flip-{date}.json`. Confirm `enforce_admins.enabled` is currently `false`.</step>
    <step order="3">Flip enforce_admins: `gh api -X POST repos/spaarke-dev/spaarke/branches/master/protection/enforce_admins`. (Note: GitHub's enforce_admins endpoint uses POST to enable / DELETE to disable.)</step>
    <step order="4">Verify required status checks INCLUDE all three: `gh api repos/spaarke-dev/spaarke/branches/master/protection/required_status_checks` and confirm the `contexts` array contains exactly `Build & Test (Debug)`, `Build & Test (Release)`, `Code Quality`. If any is missing, add via PATCH and re-verify.</step>
    <step order="5">Capture post-change snapshot: `gh api repos/spaarke-dev/spaarke/branches/master/protection > projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/ci-gate-post-flip-{date}.json`. Confirm `enforce_admins.enabled` now `true`.</step>
    <step order="6">Update `current-task.md` with pre→post diff summary + cite both snapshot file paths.</step>
    <step order="7">Verify `git status` shows changes ONLY under `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/` — no other files.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="gh">api (POST enforce_admins; PATCH required_status_checks if needed; GET verifications)</tool>
    <tool name="git">status</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/ci-gate-pre-flip-2026-MM-DD.json</output>
    <output type="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/ci-gate-post-flip-2026-MM-DD.json</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`gh api .../branches/master/protection` shows `enforce_admins.enabled: true`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`required_status_checks.contexts` includes `Build &amp; Test (Debug)`, `Build &amp; Test (Release)`, `Code Quality`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Pre + post snapshot JSONs exist in `baseline/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No modifications to `src/`, `tests/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
